From: Padmanabh Ratnakar <padmanabh.ratnakar@emulex.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Oct 2012 06:04:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 127/143] be2net: Enabling Wake-on-LAN is not supported in S5
 state
Patch-mainline: v3.8-rc1
Git-commit: 028991e49a706652cfaec06947ef755e6161a5f4
References: bnc#777565 FATE#313819

be_shutdown is enabling wake-on-lan by calling be_setup_wol.
Emulex adapter do not support wake-on-lan in S5 state.

Signed-off-by: Vasundhara Volam <vasundhara.volam@emulex.com>
Signed-off-by: Padmanabh Ratnakar <padmanabh.ratnakar@emulex.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c |    3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
@@ -4166,9 +4166,6 @@ static void be_shutdown(struct pci_dev *
 
 	netif_device_detach(adapter->netdev);
 
-	if (adapter->wol)
-		be_setup_wol(adapter, true);
-
 	be_cmd_reset_function(adapter);
 
 	pci_disable_device(pdev);
